Protective effects of endothelin antagonists in chronic renal failure.

Wolf SC(1), Brehm BR, Gaschler F, Brehm S, Klaussner M, Smykowski J, Amann K, 
Osswald H, Erley CM, Risler T.

Author information:
(1)Medical Department Tübingen, Germany.

The present study suggests that ET-1 is involved in the pathogenesis of uraemic 
cardiac hypertrophy and in the progression of renal failure in rats with 
subtotal nephrectomy examined after an intermediate period of 12 weeks of renal 
